	(960,82,'B00GTBH4Q2','','Thai Tan','Lively Activity Sensors','lively-activity-sensor','<div></div><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Lively Activity Sensor is a sensor that has been designed to give family and friends of the elderly better insight into their loved one’s daily lives, without being overly invasive. Lively Activity Sensors do not require WiFi — working instead with a built in cellular system — do not have cameras or motion sensors and are designed for privacy while still maintaining the perfect level of notification to family members. In fact, Lively Activity Sensors can be placed really anywhere the elderly and their family find important for total tracking of what is most important to you/them. Place a Lively Activity Sensor on medication bottles, on the refrigerator, on a key chain and even a bathroom door or favorite chair, and the Sensors will work together to learn your loved one’s regular routine, (when they take their medications, how often they eat, how long they usually stay out of the house for, etc), and will notify you and anyone else on the network via smartphone, tablet or laptop, through text or email. Additionally, with the Lively Activity Sensors month subscription, users are able to send various pictures and notes — downloaded straight from phones, tablets, computers or even social media accounts — and have each these be sent as hard copies (via the postal service), to their loved one’s front doors. A great way to increase the support system for you elderly family member or friend, the Lively Active Sensors are the perfect way to help both you and your loved one feel more at ease, and receives 3.4 out of 5 stars on Amazon, with users claiming it is definitely a helpful device and works pretty well, though there are a few who seem to have issues with connectivity and claim there is poor customer service.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span></span></p><ul><li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">Stay